org.microtitan.diffusive.diffuser.restful.request

Class ExecuteDiffuserRequest

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.microtitan.diffusive.diffuser.restful.request.ExecuteDiffuserRequest

  • public class ExecuteDiffuserRequest
extends java.lang.Object
    Represents the request issued to the RESTful service to execute a method within an object. This class wraps the information needed to execute that method.
    Author:
    Robert Philipp Jul 15, 2012

        public static final ExecuteDiffuserRequest create(java.lang.String returnType,
                            java.util.List<java.lang.String> argumentTypes,
                            java.util.List<byte[]> argumentValues,
                            java.lang.String serializedObjectType,
                            byte[] serializedObject,
                            java.lang.String serializerType)
        Factory method for creating a request to execute a method.
        Parameters:
        returnType - The return type class name of the method.
        argumentTypes - The class names of the methods formal parameters
        argumentValues - The serialized values of the actual parameters passed to the method
        serializedObjectType - The class name of the object whose class holds the method to be executed
        serializedObject - The serialized object that contains the method
        serializerType - The serializer type name (see SerializerFactory)
        Returns:
        The request to execute the method
